1
00:00:16,831 --> 00:00:18,123
[alarm beeps]

2
00:00:19,166 --> 00:00:21,377
[theme music playing]

3
00:00:58,706 --> 00:00:59,540
THIS IS A WORK OF FICTION

4
00:00:59,623 --> 00:01:01,125
CHILD ACTORS WERE FILMED SAFELY
WITH SUPERVISION

5
00:01:07,006 --> 00:01:09,466
Releasing my first album after 30.

6
00:01:10,843 --> 00:01:12,553
That's way beyond late,

7
00:01:13,304 --> 00:01:14,305
isn't it?

8
00:01:25,065 --> 00:01:29,320
THE 1ST ALBUM
BAND GA-EUL

9
00:01:32,406 --> 00:01:34,158
I only had one thing in mind.

10
00:01:34,783 --> 00:01:36,577
I just wanted to make it first

11
00:01:37,453 --> 00:01:38,829
and then propose to you.

12
00:01:44,376 --> 00:01:46,754
Pretty soon, I'll be signing with a label.

13
00:01:47,504 --> 00:01:50,591
And after that,
we can move into a house like you wanted.

14
00:01:52,426 --> 00:01:54,219
-Come on, let's give it another sho--
-Ga-eul.

15
00:01:56,472 --> 00:01:58,349
Do you really want us to get married?

16
00:02:07,149 --> 00:02:08,859
I don't want to break up with you.

17
00:02:10,277 --> 00:02:11,362
If we do…

18
00:02:13,280 --> 00:02:14,114
then what?

19
00:02:17,117 --> 00:02:20,245
Forcing yourself
to fit into the future that I want,

20
00:02:21,455 --> 00:02:23,582
will you really want to live like that?

21
00:02:25,417 --> 00:02:28,504
If you want,
I'll release albums more often,

22
00:02:28,587 --> 00:02:30,005
and I won't go anywhere.

23
00:02:31,006 --> 00:02:32,049
[Ji-yoon] You idiot.

24
00:02:32,675 --> 00:02:35,427
That's not the person
that I fell in love with.

25
00:02:40,599 --> 00:02:41,809
The thing is…

26
00:02:42,977 --> 00:02:45,646
I don't want you to change because of me.

27
00:02:49,900 --> 00:02:51,777
What a selfish thing to say.

28
00:02:52,820 --> 00:02:56,824
You built up all these expectations,
and now you're walking back on them.

29
00:02:59,910 --> 00:03:00,911
I am…

30
00:03:02,621 --> 00:03:04,248
too late, aren't I?

31
00:03:05,040 --> 00:03:06,208
You know me.

32
00:03:08,836 --> 00:03:11,588
I'm the kind of person who thinks
that releasing your first album

33
00:03:11,672 --> 00:03:13,632
after 30 is beyond late.

34
00:03:15,175 --> 00:03:17,970
But the thing is that
you're not just any 30-year-old.

35
00:03:19,138 --> 00:03:21,598
You actually spent all that time…

36
00:03:22,808 --> 00:03:24,435
learning music and writing lyrics.

37
00:03:26,061 --> 00:03:27,396
And pretending to travel

38
00:03:28,022 --> 00:03:30,524
while working a lot of part-time jobs.

39
00:03:34,153 --> 00:03:35,154
Oh…

40
00:03:36,780 --> 00:03:38,032
You actually knew?

41
00:03:39,366 --> 00:03:40,451
You were right, Ga-eul.

42
00:03:42,327 --> 00:03:44,079
This album wasn't ready then.

43
00:03:44,663 --> 00:03:46,915
[sighs] It had to come out now.

44
00:03:48,709 --> 00:03:49,710
You really…

45
00:03:50,669 --> 00:03:52,004
want it to end like this?

46
00:03:55,257 --> 00:03:56,258
Mm-hmm.

47
00:03:59,803 --> 00:04:00,804
[sighs]

48
00:04:00,888 --> 00:04:01,889
Ji-yoon.

49
00:04:03,307 --> 00:04:04,808
You were amazing up there.

50
00:04:06,268 --> 00:04:09,313
You were exactly the way you were
when I first fell for you.

51
00:04:09,396 --> 00:04:10,522
Ga-eul,

52
00:04:11,815 --> 00:04:13,358
just be yourself.

53
00:04:13,442 --> 00:04:14,943
Just as you are now.

54
00:04:16,403 --> 00:04:18,572
Don't change yourself to fit into my mold.

55
00:04:21,366 --> 00:04:22,743
I'll do the same thing.

56
00:04:23,660 --> 00:04:24,661
[sniffles]

57
00:04:25,913 --> 00:04:27,915
[wistful music playing]

58
00:04:33,253 --> 00:04:34,463
Thanks so much…

59
00:04:38,550 --> 00:04:40,552
for letting me see you shine on stage…

60
00:04:43,055 --> 00:04:44,723
one last time, Ga-eul.

61
00:04:47,893 --> 00:04:50,646
[sniffles, sobbing]

62
00:04:57,820 --> 00:04:59,905
[sobbing]

63
00:05:06,078 --> 00:05:09,289
And in the end, I couldn't open the album.

64
00:05:10,999 --> 00:05:14,670
It felt too much like prying open a heart

65
00:05:15,921 --> 00:05:17,673
that had barely found closure.

66
00:05:21,093 --> 00:05:26,181
EPISODE 4
BROKE UP YESTERDAY, STILL CLOCKING IN!

67
00:05:26,265 --> 00:05:27,724
Just how much did you cry?

68
00:05:28,392 --> 00:05:31,854
Enough to… [sighs]
…not leave a single drop of regret.

69
00:05:31,937 --> 00:05:33,605
You should've gotten back together.

70
00:05:33,689 --> 00:05:35,941
You said he's finally starting
to do well for himself.

71
00:05:36,024 --> 00:05:37,609
We'd end up breaking up again.

72
00:05:38,861 --> 00:05:41,697
And I'd end up looking like this again.
Puffy toad face.

73
00:05:41,780 --> 00:05:43,365
[both chuckle]

74
00:05:44,074 --> 00:05:46,743
Playing the damsel in distress
in your own movie every night

75
00:05:46,827 --> 00:05:49,413
is just what
a real relationship is all about.

76
00:05:51,290 --> 00:05:52,833
Good morning, Ms. Cha Ji-yoon!

77
00:05:52,916 --> 00:05:54,376
My name is Shin Na-ri from Marketing.

78
00:05:54,459 --> 00:05:55,335
Hi, Na-ri!

79
00:05:55,419 --> 00:05:57,462
-We were hired together.
-Okay.

80
00:05:59,089 --> 00:06:00,382
Why are you here to see me?

81
00:06:00,465 --> 00:06:03,302
Oh, I heard you're able to help
with work this weekend.

82
00:06:03,385 --> 00:06:04,344
Sorry?

83
00:06:04,428 --> 00:06:07,764
So I assume that you're free this weekend.

84
00:06:09,349 --> 00:06:12,060
She's been working overtime,
and you want her to work on the weekend?

85
00:06:12,144 --> 00:06:14,980
[chuckles] It's fine.
I actually said I could do it.

86
00:06:15,063 --> 00:06:16,273
Great.

87
00:06:17,691 --> 00:06:21,111
We're collaborating with a highball brand
to promote our ice sphere fridge.

88
00:06:21,195 --> 00:06:22,821
Oh! Baseball?

89
00:06:22,905 --> 00:06:25,449
Yeah, it's SAEUM's home game this weekend.

90
00:06:25,532 --> 00:06:27,451
All 20,000 seats are sold out.

91
00:06:27,534 --> 00:06:30,370
Don't you think it's the perfect chance
to make an impression?

92
00:06:30,454 --> 00:06:32,915
Hmm. That sounds amazing.

93
00:06:32,998 --> 00:06:34,291
Na-ri's pretty good.

94
00:06:34,791 --> 00:06:38,045
Thank you, but this project
was actually proposed by Mr. Kang himself.

95
00:06:38,128 --> 00:06:41,632
Mmm. True to form.
He's incredibly thorough.

96
00:06:41,715 --> 00:06:43,383
On that note then,

97
00:06:44,009 --> 00:06:49,014
is that why you have that look
on your face? Because of Mr. Kang?

98
00:06:49,598 --> 00:06:51,683
-I've been hearing wild rumors about him.
-[laughing] Oh, no…

99
00:06:51,767 --> 00:06:53,393
They're not rumors. It's a fact.

100
00:06:53,477 --> 00:06:55,020
Don't get me started on his attitude.

101
00:06:55,103 --> 00:06:56,355
Really?

102
00:06:56,438 --> 00:06:58,899
He's just not very talkative, you know?

103
00:06:58,982 --> 00:07:01,068
But he's not always like that.

104
00:07:01,151 --> 00:07:02,986
He's actually very kind though.

105
00:07:03,070 --> 00:07:04,154
Ms. Cha…

106
00:07:05,030 --> 00:07:08,033
Seriously?
Are you taking Mr. Kang's side right now?

107
00:07:08,617 --> 00:07:10,244
It's not that I'm taking his side…

108
00:07:10,327 --> 00:07:12,746
[gasps] Are you two perhaps… [gasps]

109
00:07:12,829 --> 00:07:14,498
Is there something between you two?

110
00:07:17,751 --> 00:07:19,169
Oh, come on. Stop that!

111
00:07:19,253 --> 00:07:23,048
Everyone knows Mr. Kang has an
insufferable way of speaking, doesn't he?

112
00:07:23,131 --> 00:07:25,634
And once he gets something on you,
he won't let it go.

113
00:07:25,717 --> 00:07:27,094
-Brutal honesty, huh?
-[coughs]

114
00:07:27,177 --> 00:07:29,429
-Sharp tongue, right? Huh?
-[clears throat]

115
00:07:29,513 --> 00:07:31,348
[Na-ri coughs]

116
00:07:42,234 --> 00:07:45,654
-We should get back to work. [chuckles]
-Mm-hmm.

117
00:07:47,990 --> 00:07:50,409
I'll contact you again later
about the project. [chuckles]

118
00:07:56,248 --> 00:07:57,416
M-Mr. Kang.

119
00:07:59,334 --> 00:08:02,045
Did you happen to hear what I said?

120
00:08:02,129 --> 00:08:03,297
Hear what exactly?

121
00:08:03,380 --> 00:08:04,589
Just now, I said…

122
00:08:04,673 --> 00:08:06,425
That I'm insufferable when I speak?

123
00:08:07,926 --> 00:08:09,511
I'm sorry, sir.

124
00:08:10,095 --> 00:08:11,388
If you say that I am,

125
00:08:11,888 --> 00:08:12,889
it must be true.

126
00:08:18,687 --> 00:08:19,813
[chuckles]

127
00:08:30,866 --> 00:08:33,577
[Si-woo] If you say that I am,
it must be true.

128
00:08:33,660 --> 00:08:35,996
If you say that I am, it must be true.

129
00:08:36,079 --> 00:08:38,248
[echoing] …it must be true.

130
00:08:41,084 --> 00:08:42,586
[sighs]

131
00:08:59,227 --> 00:09:01,480
What are we going to do
about the launch presentation?

132
00:09:01,563 --> 00:09:04,900
Since you're just riding
on someone else's coattails,

133
00:09:04,983 --> 00:09:07,361
you can't possibly be thinking
of doing it yourself, right?

134
00:09:07,944 --> 00:09:09,821
No, I have no intention to.

135
00:09:09,905 --> 00:09:11,531
Well, at least there's that.

136
00:09:12,866 --> 00:09:13,700
In that case,

137
00:09:14,284 --> 00:09:16,286
Ms. Cha, write up a draft for it.

138
00:09:16,370 --> 00:09:19,247
I'll need to revise it a few times.
So you better hurry.

139
00:09:21,666 --> 00:09:22,667
The launch…

140
00:09:23,960 --> 00:09:25,337
will be presented by Ms. Cha.

141
00:09:30,801 --> 00:09:31,802
M-Me?

142
00:09:31,885 --> 00:09:32,886
Yes.

143
00:09:33,387 --> 00:09:35,514
After all, you're the one
who has been on the project

144
00:09:35,597 --> 00:09:37,599
from the beginning
until its successful development.

145
00:09:39,309 --> 00:09:41,061
[Young-sam scoffs] Oh, please. Come on.

146
00:09:41,561 --> 00:09:43,980
Give me a break. Are you serious?

147
00:09:44,064 --> 00:09:47,234
A senior associate can't handle
a product launch presentation!

148
00:09:47,984 --> 00:09:49,486
Hey, Ms. Cha, tell him now.

149
00:09:49,569 --> 00:09:51,780
Honestly, does this make sense to you?

150
00:09:54,324 --> 00:09:58,078
If my manager is saying so,
I suppose it does.

151
00:09:59,162 --> 00:10:00,038
What?

152
00:10:00,122 --> 00:10:01,832
[Si-Woo] You are totally capable.

153
00:10:01,915 --> 00:10:05,001
You just need to do what you did
when you convinced me and Development.

154
00:10:07,796 --> 00:10:11,967
Do you think getting up on that massive
stage and giving a presentation is a joke?

155
00:10:12,050 --> 00:10:14,386
Let's not be so reckless
and ruin the whole thing!

156
00:10:14,469 --> 00:10:15,720
I will do it.

157
00:10:17,180 --> 00:10:18,265
I will.

158
00:10:18,348 --> 00:10:20,267
Hey, Ms. Cha. [clicks tongue]

159
00:10:21,977 --> 00:10:23,186
Very well.

160
00:10:23,270 --> 00:10:25,063
Don't worry, I'll help you.

161
00:10:26,064 --> 00:10:27,065
Thank you, sir.

162
00:10:29,526 --> 00:10:30,527
[grunts]

163
00:10:32,863 --> 00:10:34,948
[sighs] Seriously?

164
00:10:37,284 --> 00:10:38,285
[sighs]

165
00:10:40,537 --> 00:10:42,706
A product launch presentation?

166
00:10:43,582 --> 00:10:45,709
[groans] A new product presentation?

167
00:10:45,792 --> 00:10:47,377
[groans] Come on.

168
00:10:47,461 --> 00:10:50,881
Why do I keep digging my own grave
like this? Why? [sighs]

169
00:10:52,340 --> 00:10:53,884
Maybe it's better this way.

170
00:10:55,760 --> 00:10:58,430
At least that way
I can lose myself in the work.

171
00:11:01,016 --> 00:11:01,850
Hey, work.

172
00:11:02,517 --> 00:11:03,643
Thank you

173
00:11:04,311 --> 00:11:06,480
for helping me
forget my sadness with pain.

174
00:11:13,361 --> 00:11:19,034
THANKS A LOT FOR LETTING ME
DROWN OUT MY SADNESS WITH PAIN!

175
00:11:28,460 --> 00:11:29,628
[No-ah sighs]

176
00:11:33,965 --> 00:11:35,050
[zipper unzips]

177
00:11:36,176 --> 00:11:37,844
-[chuckles]
-[zipper zips]

178
00:11:44,643 --> 00:11:47,979
[No-ah] No-ah being proactive
and passing DELF A2!

179
00:11:53,944 --> 00:11:55,445
Please write down your name on this.

180
00:11:55,529 --> 00:11:57,614
[chuckles] I have a boyfriend.

181
00:11:58,448 --> 00:11:59,366
Good for you.

182
00:11:59,908 --> 00:12:00,742
Sorry?

183
00:12:00,825 --> 00:12:02,661
I'm getting everyone's contact info.

184
00:12:03,161 --> 00:12:04,329
I'm the TA for this class.

185
00:12:04,412 --> 00:12:07,707
Ah. Oh, I'm sorry.

186
00:12:07,791 --> 00:12:09,876
I misunderstood. Just a second.

187
00:12:14,464 --> 00:12:15,799
Here.

188
00:12:15,882 --> 00:12:17,050
YOON NO-AH
010-0705-8005

189
00:12:17,133 --> 00:12:18,301
"Yoon No-ah."

190
00:12:19,594 --> 00:12:21,930
-I'll contact you at this number.
-Sure.

191
00:12:22,013 --> 00:12:23,890
Next time, please bring my hat.

192
00:12:23,974 --> 00:12:24,808
Sorry?

193
00:12:29,938 --> 00:12:31,022
Oh.

194
00:12:31,606 --> 00:12:34,484
That hat is actually really special to me.

195
00:12:39,990 --> 00:12:42,367
[crying]

196
00:12:42,450 --> 00:12:44,202
[in French] You should hide your tears.

197
00:12:51,001 --> 00:12:52,335
[sighs]

198
00:12:53,712 --> 00:12:54,713
[chuckles]

199
00:13:06,808 --> 00:13:07,809
[in English] There's no way.

200
00:13:08,393 --> 00:13:10,937
Why not? You're actually super tall, sir.

201
00:13:11,021 --> 00:13:12,439
Not taller than the tree.

202
00:13:12,522 --> 00:13:13,982
Well, you can use this then.

203
00:13:14,065 --> 00:13:15,233
No, there's no way.

204
00:13:15,317 --> 00:13:16,359
[groans]

205
00:13:16,943 --> 00:13:18,737
What are we gonna do about that?

206
00:13:19,279 --> 00:13:21,281
I can't leave it up there and lose it.

207
00:13:24,409 --> 00:13:25,660
Get a firm grip.

208
00:13:33,084 --> 00:13:34,586
[child 1] Oh. Oh.

209
00:13:37,088 --> 00:13:39,215
-Oh! Wow!
-[child 2] Wow!

210
00:13:39,841 --> 00:13:41,551
Thank you very much, sir.

211
00:13:41,635 --> 00:13:43,887
I didn't do anything. You did it yourself.

212
00:13:43,970 --> 00:13:45,263
Okay.

213
00:13:45,889 --> 00:13:48,600
Wait. Here you go.

214
00:13:54,397 --> 00:13:55,482
Is that a gift?

215
00:14:02,530 --> 00:14:03,740
Let's go!

216
00:14:12,415 --> 00:14:14,250
[Ji-yoon] Do you not like chocolate?

217
00:14:16,127 --> 00:14:17,629
No. I do like it.

218
00:14:17,712 --> 00:14:19,089
Why that face then?

219
00:14:19,798 --> 00:14:23,593
And also, if you were gonna help them,
why did you say you couldn't at first?

220
00:14:23,677 --> 00:14:25,762
I knew that I couldn't have done it alone.

221
00:14:25,845 --> 00:14:27,972
[scoffs] This is why people…

222
00:14:28,973 --> 00:14:31,393
You know, you're the type
who's easily misunderstood.

223
00:14:31,476 --> 00:14:32,310
Know that?

224
00:14:32,394 --> 00:14:35,730
You know, the Clock-in Fairy
has been running late.

225
00:14:36,314 --> 00:14:40,110
I stayed up late last night
because of the presentation.

226
00:14:40,902 --> 00:14:43,947
I mean, I'm already short on time
preparing for the launch.

227
00:14:44,030 --> 00:14:47,033
And now you want me to help
with the Marketing Team's work.

228
00:14:47,117 --> 00:14:48,118
Two of me is a bit too--

229
00:14:48,201 --> 00:14:49,911
We're not here just to help out Marketing.

230
00:14:49,994 --> 00:14:51,079
Then what?

231
00:14:51,162 --> 00:14:53,998
You can think of this as a rehearsal
for the product launch.

232
00:14:54,082 --> 00:14:56,710
Either way, it's about
pitching the product to customers.

233
00:14:56,793 --> 00:15:00,130
Doing this today will help you figure out
an angle for your presentation.

234
00:15:00,213 --> 00:15:02,966
So, you did this for me?

235
00:15:03,049 --> 00:15:04,467
For my own sake.

236
00:15:05,301 --> 00:15:07,762
A coach gets all the blame
for choosing the wrong player.

237
00:15:16,896 --> 00:15:17,897
Let's go.

238
00:15:19,274 --> 00:15:20,567
Are you sure you like it?

239
00:15:21,151 --> 00:15:22,360
You look like you don't.

240
00:15:23,987 --> 00:15:27,407
[Na-ri] I'll be taking care of the event
and of course promoting the brand too.

241
00:15:27,490 --> 00:15:30,368
All you need to do, Ms. Cha,
is stand next to this refrigerator

242
00:15:30,452 --> 00:15:33,830
and explain all the features
and benefits of an ice sphere.

243
00:15:33,913 --> 00:15:34,956
Okay. Got it.

244
00:15:35,039 --> 00:15:36,958
As for you, Mr. Kang…

245
00:15:37,041 --> 00:15:39,210
I didn't expect you to be here too.
[chuckles]

246
00:15:39,794 --> 00:15:41,296
I'll just be handing out the brochures.

247
00:15:41,379 --> 00:15:42,672
Sure.

248
00:15:44,215 --> 00:15:46,301
In that case, here.

249
00:15:47,051 --> 00:15:49,304
I managed to secure one for Mr. Kang too.

250
00:15:59,647 --> 00:16:02,192
[gentle music playing]

251
00:16:04,402 --> 00:16:05,612
[Na-ri] Wow.

252
00:16:05,695 --> 00:16:08,031
I almost mistook him for a real player.

253
00:16:09,657 --> 00:16:13,203
He can't look like that
and work at an electronics company.

254
00:16:13,787 --> 00:16:16,539
Yeah, he has no business
working out as much as he does.

255
00:16:16,623 --> 00:16:20,627
Who cares if he's a little snarky
when he's such eye candy? [chuckles]

256
00:16:20,710 --> 00:16:24,255
Thankfully, he doesn't talk that much.

257
00:16:24,339 --> 00:16:26,174
[Na-ri gasps] That's so nice.

258
00:16:26,257 --> 00:16:27,592
[both chuckle]

259
00:16:28,176 --> 00:16:29,928
-What do you think you're doing?
-[both] Sorry?

260
00:16:30,011 --> 00:16:32,263
Can't you see all the people
waiting behind you?

261
00:16:32,347 --> 00:16:34,015
Oh! [stammers]

262
00:16:34,098 --> 00:16:35,558
Uh, I'm so sorry! [chuckles]

263
00:16:42,065 --> 00:16:44,150
-[Si-woo] We are from SAEUM.
-Hello! How are you?

264
00:16:44,234 --> 00:16:45,860
Would you like this one? This one's good.

265
00:16:45,944 --> 00:16:48,613
The fridge you see here
is SAEUM's soon-to-be-released

266
00:16:48,696 --> 00:16:50,073
Ice Sphere Refrigerator.

267
00:16:50,156 --> 00:16:52,075
Now, as to what an ice sphere is…

268
00:16:52,659 --> 00:16:54,035
Hello, we're from SAEUM.

269
00:16:54,869 --> 00:16:56,621
Uh, could I get your autograph?

270
00:16:56,704 --> 00:16:57,705
I am not a player.

271
00:16:59,916 --> 00:17:00,959
Since the game started,

272
00:17:01,042 --> 00:17:04,128
you can leave things here with us,
and go enjoy the game for a bit.

273
00:17:04,212 --> 00:17:06,422
-Is that okay?
-Yes, of course.

274
00:17:06,506 --> 00:17:08,675
Mr. Kang, let's go.

275
00:17:09,384 --> 00:17:10,218
All right, let's go.

276
00:17:10,301 --> 00:17:11,135
Yes!

277
00:17:11,219 --> 00:17:13,680
[crowd cheering]

278
00:17:18,184 --> 00:17:21,229
[crowd chanting, singing]

279
00:17:22,981 --> 00:17:24,774
♪ Victory! ♪

280
00:17:25,859 --> 00:17:28,653
[crowd continues singing]

281
00:17:28,736 --> 00:17:29,737
♪ SAEUM ♪

282
00:17:32,115 --> 00:17:33,116
[cheerleaders chanting]

283
00:17:34,701 --> 00:17:36,452
-Should we watch from here?
-Sure.

284
00:17:37,370 --> 00:17:38,496
-Oh, excuse me.
-Yes?

285
00:17:39,664 --> 00:17:41,833
Would you like one too?
They're on me this time.

286
00:17:41,916 --> 00:17:43,001
I drove here though.

287
00:17:45,587 --> 00:17:46,921
-Just one glass, please.
-Just one?

288
00:17:47,005 --> 00:17:48,006
-Thanks.
-Sure.

289
00:17:53,636 --> 00:17:55,430
-Here. Thank you.
-Thank you very much.

290
00:18:07,108 --> 00:18:09,652
[sighs] That hits the spot.

291
00:18:10,236 --> 00:18:13,031
When you're at a game,
you just can't do without a beer.

292
00:18:13,114 --> 00:18:14,949
I question your loyalty.

293
00:18:15,033 --> 00:18:18,286
You were just running a highball event,
and now you're drinking beer?

294
00:18:18,870 --> 00:18:22,081
[scoffs] Beer and my loyalty
are different things.

295
00:18:24,083 --> 00:18:25,126
Come on.

296
00:18:25,209 --> 00:18:29,547
No outs with runners on first and second.
Why keep swinging for the fence?

297
00:18:30,757 --> 00:18:32,342
What's wrong with the fences?

298
00:18:32,926 --> 00:18:35,178
Well, right now
we're actually down by one.

299
00:18:35,261 --> 00:18:36,346
In times like these,

300
00:18:36,429 --> 00:18:39,015
he should just be thinking
of getting one more run with a sac bunt.

301
00:18:39,098 --> 00:18:41,017
A single hit could turn the game.

302
00:18:41,100 --> 00:18:43,353
If I were the coach,
I'd tell them to be aggressive

303
00:18:43,436 --> 00:18:44,729
even if he ends up striking out.

304
00:18:44,812 --> 00:18:47,148
[crowd chanting]

305
00:18:47,231 --> 00:18:50,068
[chanting continues]

306
00:18:50,985 --> 00:18:52,862
[groaning]

307
00:18:53,446 --> 00:18:54,447
[stammers] Oh!

308
00:19:05,083 --> 00:19:09,253
[calm music playing]

309
00:19:10,713 --> 00:19:13,925
[commentator 1] Wow, a spectator
caught it. And with his bare hands too.

310
00:19:14,008 --> 00:19:15,551
-[crowd cheering]
-[commentator 2] Wow.

311
00:19:15,635 --> 00:19:18,972
I think he moved his hand out of reflex
just so his girlfriend wouldn't get hit.

312
00:19:19,055 --> 00:19:20,890
[commentator 1] Is this the power of love?

313
00:19:26,980 --> 00:19:28,147
Thank you so much, sir.

314
00:19:28,231 --> 00:19:30,441
Shouldn't you know
how to avoid getting hit?

315
00:19:30,525 --> 00:19:33,861
Well, oddly enough,
I freeze up when I panic.

316
00:19:33,945 --> 00:19:35,738
That's because you don't work out.

317
00:19:35,822 --> 00:19:37,365
You should work out three times a week.

318
00:19:38,199 --> 00:19:40,368
[sighs] Thank you. [gasps]

319
00:19:41,786 --> 00:19:44,497
Mr. Kang! Wait, is your hand okay?

320
00:19:44,580 --> 00:19:45,581
Oh, no.

321
00:19:45,665 --> 00:19:47,625
It's all red and swollen.

322
00:19:47,709 --> 00:19:49,585
I mean, you can't just tell me to duck

323
00:19:49,669 --> 00:19:52,088
and then just go for it like it's nothing!

324
00:19:52,171 --> 00:19:54,507
-What are you, a baseball player?
-It does hurt.

325
00:19:54,590 --> 00:19:57,135
Yeah, I bet. Oh, my goodness.

326
00:19:57,218 --> 00:19:58,302
Oh, what should we do?

327
00:19:58,386 --> 00:20:00,054
That's making it hurt more.

328
00:20:12,400 --> 00:20:14,986
[crowd exclaiming, cheering]

329
00:20:15,069 --> 00:20:16,821
[romantic music playing]

330
00:20:21,200 --> 00:20:23,077
[chuckling]

331
00:20:25,913 --> 00:20:27,415
[spectator exclaims]

332
00:20:27,999 --> 00:20:31,252
[commentator 1] Oh, that's the couple
who caught the ball barehanded earlier.

333
00:20:31,335 --> 00:20:33,671
Are you two not a couple?

334
00:20:34,297 --> 00:20:36,507
You're not? Oh.

335
00:20:37,091 --> 00:20:38,718
Then, how about you

336
00:20:38,801 --> 00:20:40,219
start dating today!

337
00:20:40,303 --> 00:20:43,681
-Give her a kiss! Give her a kiss!
-[crowd chanting] Give her a kiss!

338
00:20:43,765 --> 00:20:48,019
[commentator 1, crowd chanting]
Give her a kiss! Give her a kiss!

339
00:20:53,983 --> 00:20:54,984
[friend] Is this your sister?

340
00:20:55,068 --> 00:20:57,737
[crowd cheering on phone]

341
00:20:57,820 --> 00:21:00,031
-[commentator 1 chattering]
-Hey, Mom. Mom!

342
00:21:00,114 --> 00:21:02,158
-Yes?
-Come over here.

343
00:21:02,742 --> 00:21:04,327
-Look at this.
-What?

344
00:21:04,410 --> 00:21:06,537
[commentator 1, crowd]
Give her a kiss! Give her a kiss!

345
00:21:06,621 --> 00:21:08,956
-Is that your sister?
-It does look like your daughter.

346
00:21:09,832 --> 00:21:11,667
Who's the man she's with?

347
00:21:13,711 --> 00:21:14,545
Don't know.

348
00:21:14,629 --> 00:21:19,050
-[chanting continues]
-[mother] Hmm?

349
00:21:19,133 --> 00:21:22,512
[chanting continues]

350
00:21:22,595 --> 00:21:25,389
What… What do we do?

351
00:21:27,058 --> 00:21:28,059
Excuse me a moment.

352
00:21:32,897 --> 00:21:35,358
[chanting fades]

353
00:21:51,833 --> 00:21:55,169
[crowd cheering]

354
00:21:58,381 --> 00:22:01,050
[crowd groaning, exclaiming]

355
00:22:03,010 --> 00:22:05,638
[comical music playing]

356
00:22:13,312 --> 00:22:15,940
The event was a great success,
thanks to you both.

357
00:22:16,023 --> 00:22:17,525
Thank you so much.

358
00:22:17,608 --> 00:22:19,610
Don't mention it. I had fun too.

359
00:22:19,694 --> 00:22:21,988
Oh. I'll get the survey results

360
00:22:22,071 --> 00:22:25,825
and get them to you by Monday.
Would that be okay with you, Mr. Kang?

361
00:22:25,908 --> 00:22:27,368
All right. Great work today.

362
00:22:27,952 --> 00:22:30,705
Mr. Kang,
now that I've worked closely with you,

363
00:22:30,788 --> 00:22:33,624
I get why Ms. Cha said
what she said about you.

364
00:22:35,960 --> 00:22:37,879
No, back then, I just…

365
00:22:37,962 --> 00:22:40,173
Anything else,
besides how insufferable I am?

366
00:22:40,256 --> 00:22:42,550
Yes. [chuckles]
She said you don't talk much,

367
00:22:42,633 --> 00:22:44,510
but that you're actually very kind.

368
00:22:45,303 --> 00:22:47,597
When exactly did I say "very," huh?

369
00:22:48,264 --> 00:22:49,265
I actually said "kind of."

370
00:22:49,348 --> 00:22:51,142
-Did you? Either way.
-Mmm.

371
00:22:51,767 --> 00:22:53,603
Well, see you at work then.

372
00:22:53,686 --> 00:22:56,189
Okay! Have a good afternoon.

373
00:22:58,774 --> 00:23:00,026
It's true though.

374
00:23:01,777 --> 00:23:03,070
I didn't say "very."

375
00:23:04,113 --> 00:23:04,947
Okay.

376
00:23:05,031 --> 00:23:08,409
I wasn't the one who started
talking about you first, either.

377
00:23:09,243 --> 00:23:12,705
It's just that everyone seems to have
the wrong idea about you.

378
00:23:12,788 --> 00:23:14,123
Yes, I know.

379
00:23:17,126 --> 00:23:18,836
[calm music playing]

380
00:23:20,338 --> 00:23:21,339
Thank you for that.

381
00:23:21,923 --> 00:23:22,798
For what?

382
00:23:22,882 --> 00:23:24,508
For actually believing me.

383
00:23:32,308 --> 00:23:34,143
Let's just take my car.

384
00:23:34,227 --> 00:23:37,104
I've made you work on the weekend,
so dinner is on me today.

385
00:23:37,772 --> 00:23:38,773
Oh.

386
00:23:39,482 --> 00:23:41,859
I'm so sorry,
I already have plans tonight.

387
00:23:41,943 --> 00:23:42,944
Right.

388
00:23:43,444 --> 00:23:45,154
Well, I guess I'll see you Monday.

389
00:23:45,238 --> 00:23:46,280
Sir.

390
00:23:51,661 --> 00:23:52,662
[sighs]

391
00:24:09,262 --> 00:24:10,388
[sighs]

392
00:24:11,305 --> 00:24:15,101
Come to think of it, we've never
even had a proper meal together.

393
00:24:23,234 --> 00:24:24,402
[sighs]

394
00:24:29,615 --> 00:24:31,534
CHO GA-EUL

395
00:24:33,244 --> 00:24:36,038
[sighs] Didn't they break up already?

396
00:24:37,873 --> 00:24:40,459
LIKE A CAT

397
00:24:40,543 --> 00:24:44,505
[in Korean] ♪ I don't know when it began ♪

398
00:24:44,588 --> 00:24:46,382
[sighs, chuckling]

399
00:24:46,465 --> 00:24:48,342
♪ Your gaze
Made every part of me breathe ♪

400
00:24:48,426 --> 00:24:49,677
[in English] What am I doing?

401
00:24:53,306 --> 00:24:55,141
TIER 1 BEEF

402
00:24:57,727 --> 00:24:59,895
Wow, this is so good.

403
00:24:59,979 --> 00:25:02,982
You should've just gotten
the best one while you were at it.

404
00:25:05,318 --> 00:25:06,861
[Ji-yoon] This is Prime grade.

405
00:25:06,944 --> 00:25:10,823
I thought Prime was the very top,
because that's what you've always been.

406
00:25:10,906 --> 00:25:11,991
But just like with beef,

407
00:25:12,074 --> 00:25:15,161
it turns out there were higher tiers
above you all along too.

408
00:25:15,244 --> 00:25:16,787
You're not making any sense.

409
00:25:16,871 --> 00:25:19,749
Mom had a matchmaking agency
actually run your numbers.

410
00:25:19,832 --> 00:25:22,084
And why would you do such a thing?

411
00:25:22,752 --> 00:25:23,753
Okay, so?

412
00:25:24,503 --> 00:25:25,463
What tier am I then?

413
00:25:27,131 --> 00:25:28,674
Out of fifteen tiers,

414
00:25:28,758 --> 00:25:29,717
you're a nine.

415
00:25:30,343 --> 00:25:32,386
-Not exactly flattering. [chuckles]
-[scoffs]

416
00:25:33,095 --> 00:25:34,847
Why am I a Tier 9? Huh?

417
00:25:34,930 --> 00:25:38,267
Well, above you, there are professionals
like doctors and lawyers

418
00:25:38,351 --> 00:25:40,019
or very good-looking celebrities.

419
00:25:40,770 --> 00:25:43,230
Apparently, to be rated at the top,
you need to have rich parents.

420
00:25:43,314 --> 00:25:44,231
[scoffs]

421
00:25:44,315 --> 00:25:47,818
What, so they can leech off their parents
even after marriage or what?

422
00:25:47,902 --> 00:25:49,320
That's just so ridiculous.

423
00:25:49,403 --> 00:25:51,906
They even asked if you'd be okay with
being with someone divorced.

424
00:25:51,989 --> 00:25:54,617
Mom, why? What's gotten into you?

425
00:25:54,700 --> 00:25:57,745
What happened to telling me
I should never get married,

426
00:25:57,828 --> 00:25:59,455
and I should just focus on my career?

427
00:25:59,538 --> 00:26:02,666
I said that because
I was worried you'd marry that punk.

428
00:26:03,209 --> 00:26:05,586
But now, your Mom has a new goal in mind.

429
00:26:06,295 --> 00:26:07,296
What kind of goal?

430
00:26:07,380 --> 00:26:09,131
I'm gonna get you married off,

431
00:26:09,965 --> 00:26:12,301
-and then I'm separating.
-What?

432
00:26:12,385 --> 00:26:15,179
-And me?
-And then I'm getting a divorce.

433
00:26:16,222 --> 00:26:17,223
Mom!

434
00:26:17,890 --> 00:26:20,684
It's bad enough that you've
kicked Dad out of his room. Really?

435
00:26:20,768 --> 00:26:23,687
He comes in when we're all asleep
and leaves after breakfast.

436
00:26:23,771 --> 00:26:25,106
[sighs]

437
00:26:26,482 --> 00:26:27,483
Who was that man?

438
00:26:27,566 --> 00:26:29,110
Who are you talking about?

439
00:26:29,193 --> 00:26:31,278
-The man you were with at the game.
-[sighs]

440
00:26:31,362 --> 00:26:33,614
You got caught on the kiss cam.

441
00:26:33,697 --> 00:26:35,616
He's my boss at work.

442
00:26:36,617 --> 00:26:38,369
He's the manager of the team I'm on.

443
00:26:38,953 --> 00:26:40,037
Is he married?

444
00:26:41,205 --> 00:26:43,916
If he's a manager at Ji-yoon's company,
he probably is.

445
00:26:43,999 --> 00:26:46,752
And his salary must be like his face.

446
00:26:46,836 --> 00:26:48,796
-He's pretty good-looking.
-[sighs]

447
00:26:48,879 --> 00:26:51,215
[sighs] I really liked Ga-eul, though.

448
00:26:51,715 --> 00:26:53,926
Yeah, but Ga-eul had no money whatsoever.

449
00:26:54,009 --> 00:26:56,387
Other than that, he was very nice.

450
00:26:56,470 --> 00:27:00,516
Ga-eul's doing pretty well nowadays.
He's got an album and tons of concerts.

451
00:27:00,599 --> 00:27:02,017
He probably earns a ton of money.

452
00:27:02,101 --> 00:27:03,144
-Really?
-Uh-huh.

453
00:27:03,227 --> 00:27:04,687
Then maybe you should get back together.

454
00:27:05,563 --> 00:27:08,816
This… This is exactly the reason
why I hate coming home.

455
00:27:08,899 --> 00:27:12,319
I don't care if you and Dad
get a divorce or just separate.

456
00:27:12,403 --> 00:27:13,779
Just stay out of my love life.

457
00:27:16,031 --> 00:27:18,325
There she goes with that temper of hers.

458
00:27:18,409 --> 00:27:20,661
She's exactly like her damn father.

459
00:27:21,162 --> 00:27:22,580
I don't share your thoughts.

460
00:27:24,457 --> 00:27:26,959
I mean, what kind of mother
wants to marry her daughter off

461
00:27:27,042 --> 00:27:28,544
so she can finally separate?

462
00:27:28,627 --> 00:27:30,254
[Hye-ji] Why not? I understand her.

463
00:27:30,337 --> 00:27:32,756
It's every parent's wish
to marry their kids off

464
00:27:32,840 --> 00:27:34,842
with a perfectly clean marriage record.

465
00:27:35,342 --> 00:27:37,261
But who even thinks divorce is a flaw…

466
00:27:38,220 --> 00:27:40,514
[sighs] I mean…

467
00:27:40,598 --> 00:27:44,560
I used to cheer when I heard
about couples splitting later in life,

468
00:27:44,643 --> 00:27:47,938
but the second it's my own parents,
my heart shatters into pieces.

469
00:27:48,022 --> 00:27:52,610
That's why divorce is completely different
from just breaking up after dating.

470
00:27:53,777 --> 00:27:56,614
It's a decision made
with the entire family in mind.

471
00:27:57,615 --> 00:28:00,451
Meaning it carries the tears
of so many more lives.

472
00:28:02,411 --> 00:28:03,954
It must've been really hard.

473
00:28:04,038 --> 00:28:05,706
For who? Your mom?

474
00:28:05,789 --> 00:28:09,376
Oh, not her. Someone else who's divorced.

475
00:28:10,336 --> 00:28:12,338
[jazz music playing on speakers]

476
00:28:19,261 --> 00:28:21,472
Why are you here alone?
You should've come with Ms. Ji-yoon.

477
00:28:21,555 --> 00:28:23,641
Since when is she "Ms. Ji-yoon"?

478
00:28:23,724 --> 00:28:25,100
What do I call her then?

479
00:28:25,184 --> 00:28:26,685
Shall I call her "Ms. Cha" too?

480
00:28:27,478 --> 00:28:28,479
She had plans.

481
00:28:28,562 --> 00:28:30,064
[sighs] Figures.

482
00:28:30,147 --> 00:28:32,149
Who would want to be
with their boss on the weekend?

483
00:28:32,233 --> 00:28:34,902
You should've treated her better
in the first place.

484
00:28:34,985 --> 00:28:38,030
I bet you've been hounding her
for being bad at her job.

485
00:28:38,113 --> 00:28:39,615
Ms. Cha's good at her job.

486
00:28:40,157 --> 00:28:42,243
She's the best employee
I've ever worked with.

487
00:28:42,326 --> 00:28:44,495
You have a soft spot for competent women.

488
00:28:44,578 --> 00:28:46,664
And for competent men as well.

489
00:28:46,747 --> 00:28:47,998
I've just never seen one.

490
00:28:48,082 --> 00:28:50,876
That's not what I meant.
I mean… [clicks tongue]

491
00:28:50,960 --> 00:28:52,836
Do you have… hmm…

492
00:28:53,837 --> 00:28:55,798
feelings for Ms. Ji-yoon?

493
00:29:04,890 --> 00:29:06,308
Huh? What was that?

494
00:29:12,565 --> 00:29:14,233
Stop meddling. It's rude.

495
00:29:17,319 --> 00:29:19,697
[scoffs] That punk.

496
00:29:20,614 --> 00:29:22,700
[calm music playing]

497
00:29:24,785 --> 00:29:27,663
[panting]

498
00:29:39,091 --> 00:29:42,177
[song continues through earphones]

499
00:29:46,390 --> 00:29:48,559
[song distorts, stops]

500
00:30:00,112 --> 00:30:02,615
YEONG-MOOK REPAIR SERVICES

501
00:30:07,286 --> 00:30:08,287
Hello, sir.

502
00:30:09,580 --> 00:30:12,333
Do you repair cassette players here
by any chance?

503
00:30:13,292 --> 00:30:15,210
The one I have suddenly
just stopped working.

504
00:30:17,504 --> 00:30:18,672
[sighs]

505
00:30:18,756 --> 00:30:19,965
Ma'am,

506
00:30:20,799 --> 00:30:23,802
this was discontinued in '98.
There won't be spare parts.

507
00:30:23,886 --> 00:30:27,514
[groans] That's right. What kind
of father gifts their kid this thing

508
00:30:27,598 --> 00:30:29,475
when everyone else was listening to CDs?

509
00:30:30,059 --> 00:30:32,645
And a secondhand piece of junk
he fixed up, no less.

510
00:30:32,728 --> 00:30:33,896
You liked it back then.

511
00:30:33,979 --> 00:30:35,272
Yes, I did.

512
00:30:36,065 --> 00:30:38,984
Plugged my headphones in
and I was the coolest kid in school.

513
00:30:39,068 --> 00:30:40,027
Geez.

514
00:30:40,110 --> 00:30:41,737
And you've been using this all this time?

515
00:30:41,820 --> 00:30:43,906
You know, they're back in style now.

516
00:30:43,989 --> 00:30:45,282
Retro, right?

517
00:30:45,366 --> 00:30:47,618
[laughs] Retro, my foot.

518
00:30:47,701 --> 00:30:49,453
[tender music playing]

519
00:30:49,536 --> 00:30:50,913
Let's see here…

520
00:30:56,627 --> 00:30:59,588
Hey, Dad, why did you marry Mom?

521
00:30:59,672 --> 00:31:01,507
Because I wanted to be with her.

522
00:31:01,590 --> 00:31:03,676
Then why do you
make her feel lonely like that?

523
00:31:04,843 --> 00:31:05,928
Did she say something again?

524
00:31:06,011 --> 00:31:07,262
She didn't.

525
00:31:08,138 --> 00:31:12,267
But I mean, let's be honest, Dad.
You're a total zero as husband material.

526
00:31:12,351 --> 00:31:14,395
You're always obsessing
over broken stereos,

527
00:31:14,478 --> 00:31:16,355
and you barely even come home.

528
00:31:16,438 --> 00:31:18,315
If I were her, I'd want to leave you too.

529
00:31:18,899 --> 00:31:20,234
I know. I know.

530
00:31:20,818 --> 00:31:22,528
But when… [sighs]

531
00:31:23,070 --> 00:31:26,573
I mean, whenever someone
walks through that door, I just soften up.

532
00:31:27,741 --> 00:31:31,036
Because to some,
it doesn't matter the cost

533
00:31:31,120 --> 00:31:32,579
or the time it takes,

534
00:31:33,080 --> 00:31:34,957
it's memories they want to repair.

535
00:31:35,040 --> 00:31:36,208
I know. [sighs]

536
00:31:36,917 --> 00:31:40,838
But maybe you could work
on keeping Mom's memories alive too. Huh?

537
00:31:40,921 --> 00:31:43,340
At this rate,
she'll just end up hating you.

538
00:31:43,424 --> 00:31:46,343
Well, this place is bound
to close down soon anyway.

539
00:31:46,427 --> 00:31:49,513
Besides, hardly anyone comes by anymore.

540
00:31:53,976 --> 00:31:55,436
Hmm. What's this?

541
00:31:56,395 --> 00:31:58,313
Does mom know you splurged?

542
00:31:58,397 --> 00:31:59,815
That was actually a gift.

543
00:31:59,898 --> 00:32:01,024
Hey, hey, hey.

544
00:32:01,108 --> 00:32:02,109
Careful.

545
00:32:02,192 --> 00:32:05,028
Hold on.
Who would gift this kind of thing to you?

546
00:32:05,112 --> 00:32:06,363
Some guy.

547
00:32:07,489 --> 00:32:09,867
A punk who's been coming here
since he was a kid.

548
00:32:09,950 --> 00:32:10,784
What?

549
00:32:11,869 --> 00:32:14,371
[Yeong-mook] He once took apart
his home stereo, broke it,

550
00:32:14,455 --> 00:32:15,914
and then he brought it here.

551
00:32:15,998 --> 00:32:17,916
I told him, "Sure, well,
if you're that curious,

552
00:32:18,000 --> 00:32:19,752
you can come here
and tinker all you want."

553
00:32:19,835 --> 00:32:21,628
[chuckles] And he's been
coming here ever since.

554
00:32:21,712 --> 00:32:23,088
What does this guy actually do?

555
00:32:23,172 --> 00:32:24,673
Isn't that sketchy?

556
00:32:24,757 --> 00:32:26,049
Why would it be sketchy?

557
00:32:27,384 --> 00:32:29,845
He just comes to fix broken stuff
and then leaves.

558
00:32:29,928 --> 00:32:31,096
Just?

559
00:32:31,180 --> 00:32:33,515
Well, it's nice to have him around.
It keeps me from getting bored.

560
00:32:33,599 --> 00:32:34,850
[exclaims, scoffs]

561
00:32:34,933 --> 00:32:37,352
It sounds like you enjoy his company
more than your daughter's.

562
00:32:37,436 --> 00:32:40,522
My goodness. How could I ever do that?

563
00:32:40,606 --> 00:32:42,357
-[chuckles]
-[chuckles]

564
00:32:43,567 --> 00:32:45,110
He should be here soon.

565
00:32:45,194 --> 00:32:46,195
[knocks on door]

566
00:32:51,158 --> 00:32:52,326
Oh, you're here.

567
00:32:54,745 --> 00:32:55,746
What's that?

568
00:32:56,497 --> 00:32:59,541
[Yeong-mook] Oh, my daughter
left me something she needed me to repair.

569
00:33:00,042 --> 00:33:02,252
Oh, is that the daughter
who asks a lot of questions?

570
00:33:02,336 --> 00:33:03,337
[Yeong-mook chuckles]

571
00:33:03,420 --> 00:33:05,798
She's a real handful, that one.

572
00:33:06,465 --> 00:33:08,926
Ever since she was a kid,
she was always curious.

573
00:33:09,009 --> 00:33:12,387
Why is this like this?
Why is that like that? [chuckles]

574
00:33:13,388 --> 00:33:18,477
And still, just looking at her
makes me smile. [chuckles]

575
00:33:18,560 --> 00:33:20,395
Right, some are like that.

576
00:33:23,649 --> 00:33:25,526
Mind if I give that a go?

577
00:33:25,609 --> 00:33:26,693
Really?

578
00:33:27,778 --> 00:33:28,779
Go ahead.

579
00:33:39,706 --> 00:33:42,709
[whimsical music playing]

580
00:34:41,018 --> 00:34:42,019
[sighs]

581
00:34:43,270 --> 00:34:45,647
Whoa, I saw him over the weekend,

582
00:34:46,857 --> 00:34:48,734
and now he's in my dreams too.

583
00:34:49,318 --> 00:34:50,319
[scoffs]

584
00:34:53,822 --> 00:34:54,990
[groans]

585
00:34:56,825 --> 00:34:58,827
[automated voice] Doors opening.

586
00:35:02,789 --> 00:35:04,583
Doors closing.

587
00:35:06,752 --> 00:35:08,879
SUNNY

588
00:35:18,013 --> 00:35:20,140
[employee] Breaking news!
Office romance! Kiss me!

589
00:35:20,223 --> 00:35:22,267
Three-No-Man and Clock-out Fairy
caught on the kiss cam!

590
00:35:22,351 --> 00:35:23,644
[laughs] What the…

591
00:35:26,021 --> 00:35:27,522
[employee 2 gasps]
Why were they at the game?

592
00:35:27,606 --> 00:35:29,524
-[employee 3] Did they kiss?
-[employee 4 laughs] On a date?

593
00:35:29,608 --> 00:35:30,859
[employee 5] Nah, no way.

594
00:35:30,943 --> 00:35:32,861
-[chuckles] Wait… What's this?
-What?

595
00:35:32,945 --> 00:35:34,071
What is this?

596
00:35:35,656 --> 00:35:37,616
Seriously, what is wrong with everyone?

597
00:35:37,699 --> 00:35:40,327
Why make such a big deal
when a man and a woman are seen together?

598
00:35:40,410 --> 00:35:42,162
So hurry up and clear things up

599
00:35:42,245 --> 00:35:44,498
-before it gets more awkward for Ms. Cha.
-Right.

600
00:35:45,082 --> 00:35:48,043
"Hello, everyone.
This is Shin Na-ri from Marketing.

601
00:35:48,126 --> 00:35:49,252
Last weekend,

602
00:35:49,336 --> 00:35:51,588
Manager Kang Si-woo
and Sr. Associate Cha Ji-yoon

603
00:35:51,672 --> 00:35:55,425
were assisting the Marketing Team
with an event at the baseball stadium.

604
00:35:55,509 --> 00:35:57,761
I hope there are
no further misunderstandings."

605
00:35:59,471 --> 00:36:00,347
Mmm.

606
00:36:00,430 --> 00:36:02,683
SHIN NA-RI
REPLY FROM ELECTROCUTED MAN

607
00:36:02,766 --> 00:36:05,227
[employee] He made her work
on the weekend? Mr. Kang is ruthless.

608
00:36:05,310 --> 00:36:07,604
[employee 2] Insane.
Good thing I didn't join the task force.

609
00:36:07,688 --> 00:36:09,731
[employee 3] She'll end up being
thrown out like yesterday's trash.

610
00:36:09,815 --> 00:36:11,149
[employee 4] Run away, Ms. "C"!

611
00:36:11,233 --> 00:36:13,318
[employee 5] "Three-No-Man"?
No. "Three-No-Hope."

612
00:36:13,902 --> 00:36:15,696
Are you sure that didn't make it worse?

613
00:36:17,823 --> 00:36:20,951
[sighs] It's better than having
strange rumors going around.

614
00:36:21,868 --> 00:36:22,953
Do you think they saw this too?

615
00:36:23,036 --> 00:36:25,080
Mm-mmm. Ms. Cha doesn't read this.

616
00:36:25,163 --> 00:36:27,249
[sighs] Thank goodness.

617
00:36:31,420 --> 00:36:33,630
SHIN NA-RI
REPLY FROM ELECTROCUTED MAN

618
00:36:33,714 --> 00:36:34,923
[scoffs]

619
00:36:35,549 --> 00:36:37,759
But isn't it obvious
that we were just working?

620
00:36:37,843 --> 00:36:40,804
Plus, shouldn't people just drop it?

621
00:36:40,887 --> 00:36:42,973
Why make Mr. Kang be the Grim Reaper?

622
00:36:43,056 --> 00:36:44,307
-[footsteps approaching]
-[scoffs]

623
00:36:44,391 --> 00:36:47,019
-[employee giggling] So funny.
-[employee 2 laughs]

624
00:36:47,602 --> 00:36:50,397
-Hey, did you see the kiss cam?
-Yes! I got so excited.

625
00:36:50,480 --> 00:36:52,107
But I heard they were just working.

626
00:36:52,190 --> 00:36:53,191
[scoffs] What a bummer.

627
00:36:53,984 --> 00:36:57,946
[employee] I mean, the camera
wouldn't just film them for no reason.

628
00:36:58,030 --> 00:37:00,824
They must've appeared
lovey-dovey or something.

629
00:37:00,907 --> 00:37:01,908
That's right.

630
00:37:01,992 --> 00:37:04,578
You could tell by their vibe
that they had something going on.

631
00:37:04,661 --> 00:37:05,746
We'll wait and see

632
00:37:06,329 --> 00:37:10,083
whether Ms. Cha becomes another victim
of Three-No-Man or not.

633
00:37:10,167 --> 00:37:12,169
[both giggling]

634
00:37:12,252 --> 00:37:14,629
-[employee 2] Seriously. Let's go.
-We shall see.

635
00:37:14,713 --> 00:37:16,214
-[both chuckle]
-[door opens]

636
00:37:18,925 --> 00:37:21,011
I'm not being anyone's victim.

637
00:37:25,307 --> 00:37:26,433
[Ji-yoon] Mr. Kang,

638
00:37:26,516 --> 00:37:29,770
I really need to do a good job
with this launch.

639
00:37:29,853 --> 00:37:32,022
So please, would you help me?

640
00:37:33,690 --> 00:37:35,150
I like for things to be perfect.

641
00:37:35,776 --> 00:37:36,777
Yes, I am aware.

642
00:37:36,860 --> 00:37:39,529
Therefore, I'm going to hold you
to a very high standard.

643
00:37:39,613 --> 00:37:40,572
I am prepared for that.

644
00:37:40,655 --> 00:37:42,115
Sure you won't regret this?

645
00:37:43,575 --> 00:37:44,576
Yes.

646
00:37:46,161 --> 00:37:47,412
Wow.

647
00:37:47,496 --> 00:37:50,040
He's even giving her presentation lessons.

648
00:37:50,916 --> 00:37:53,668
Isn't assigning the presentation
to Ms. Cha a punishment?

649
00:37:53,752 --> 00:37:55,921
I get he dislikes Mr. Ko, but still.

650
00:37:56,546 --> 00:37:57,839
As long as she does well,

651
00:37:58,590 --> 00:38:00,342
it's an opportunity for her too.

652
00:38:01,384 --> 00:38:02,928
It's all true, but…

653
00:38:03,762 --> 00:38:04,596
But?

654
00:38:04,679 --> 00:38:07,682
You know that employee
who took a leave of absence for therapy

655
00:38:07,766 --> 00:38:09,267
while working under Mr. Kang?

656
00:38:09,351 --> 00:38:10,685
I looked into it.

657
00:38:10,769 --> 00:38:15,524
And apparently, he ended up like that
during a product launch presentation.

658
00:38:16,024 --> 00:38:17,025
Are you serious?

659
00:38:17,109 --> 00:38:18,485
[Kee-tae] Yeah.

660
00:38:18,568 --> 00:38:21,029
He must've buckled under the pressure
of the presentation.

661
00:38:21,613 --> 00:38:23,657
He did all the prep work, but in the end,

662
00:38:24,324 --> 00:38:25,909
it was Mr. Kang who presented.

663
00:38:25,992 --> 00:38:29,371
[employee] Is Mr. Kang a pro
at riding others' coattails or what?

664
00:38:29,454 --> 00:38:30,705
It's all or nothing.

665
00:38:31,206 --> 00:38:34,417
It's either a jackpot or a total bust.

666
00:38:34,501 --> 00:38:38,130
[sighs, groans] This must be
so nerve-racking for Ms. Cha.

667
00:38:41,842 --> 00:38:46,680
…transforms an ordinary drink
into an experience…

668
00:38:49,141 --> 00:38:51,434
-[groans] Awkward, right?
-What do you think the problem is?

669
00:38:51,518 --> 00:38:54,855
The way I'm saying things,
and my tone's off.

670
00:38:54,938 --> 00:38:56,314
Well, none of that matters.

671
00:38:56,398 --> 00:38:57,482
Then what?

672
00:38:57,566 --> 00:39:00,402
The self-confidence in knowing
that you have created a gem.

673
00:39:00,485 --> 00:39:02,696
That's what's missing
from your speech right now.

674
00:39:03,613 --> 00:39:04,865
Focus on your delivery.

675
00:39:04,948 --> 00:39:07,659
There will be subtitles anyway,
so it doesn't matter if they can't hear.

676
00:39:07,742 --> 00:39:11,121
But be a little more
arrogant and confident.

677
00:39:11,204 --> 00:39:12,539
Try it again.

678
00:39:12,622 --> 00:39:13,623
Okay.

679
00:39:14,541 --> 00:39:15,542
[sighs]

680
00:39:16,418 --> 00:39:18,670
With less surface and area in contact…

681
00:39:19,254 --> 00:39:20,172
Smile.

682
00:39:21,214 --> 00:39:24,342
-…with your drink…
-Your gestures need to be

683
00:39:24,968 --> 00:39:27,095
bolder and bigger.

684
00:39:29,097 --> 00:39:32,517
-…the ice melts slowly…
-Drop your shoulders,

685
00:39:34,102 --> 00:39:35,228
and tuck your chin.

686
00:39:36,021 --> 00:39:38,106
…preserving flavor longer…

687
00:39:39,691 --> 00:39:40,859
Eyes steady.

688
00:39:42,986 --> 00:39:43,987
…and above all…

689
00:39:49,117 --> 00:39:50,327
it's beautiful.

690
00:39:58,835 --> 00:39:59,878
Let's try again.

691
00:40:00,795 --> 00:40:02,339
Remember everything I just said.

692
00:40:02,964 --> 00:40:03,965
Sir.

693
00:40:08,929 --> 00:40:10,055
Thank you, sir.

694
00:40:11,056 --> 00:40:12,682
How many cups of coffee
have you had today?

695
00:40:12,766 --> 00:40:16,228
Uh, around two, three, or four?

696
00:40:16,311 --> 00:40:18,563
I'm sure I told you
that caffeine aggravates anxiety.

697
00:40:18,647 --> 00:40:20,690
I also drank a lot of chamomile tea.

698
00:40:20,774 --> 00:40:22,484
Do you think chamomile
is some kind of antidote?

699
00:40:22,567 --> 00:40:25,904
Well, I mean, I'm sure it's better
than not drinking anything at all.

700
00:40:28,907 --> 00:40:29,991
[chuckles]

701
00:40:32,035 --> 00:40:33,203
[clears throat]

702
00:40:34,829 --> 00:40:36,915
-[chuckles]
-[elevator bell dings]

703
00:40:44,798 --> 00:40:45,840
Ms. Choi.

704
00:40:46,591 --> 00:40:47,926
[chuckles] Please.

705
00:41:04,109 --> 00:41:05,902
Ms. Choi, I see you're back already.

706
00:41:05,986 --> 00:41:06,987
Mm-hmm.

707
00:41:07,946 --> 00:41:09,864
Did you enjoy your honeymoon?

708
00:41:14,077 --> 00:41:15,662
Mmm, it was amazing.

709
00:41:16,705 --> 00:41:18,540
I saw you switched teams though.

710
00:41:19,040 --> 00:41:19,916
Yes.

711
00:41:24,546 --> 00:41:25,714
I was worried about it,

712
00:41:26,423 --> 00:41:27,716
but you seem well.

713
00:41:32,095 --> 00:41:33,555
[elevator bell dings]

714
00:41:36,391 --> 00:41:38,268
Hello there, Mr. Ko.

715
00:41:45,358 --> 00:41:49,237
You know, I tend to get lucky whenever
I meet you in an elevator, Ms. Choi.

716
00:41:49,321 --> 00:41:51,114
I guess something good's about to happen.

717
00:41:51,197 --> 00:41:52,490
[chuckles] Is that so?

718
00:41:52,574 --> 00:41:54,451
Mmm, that's such a nice thing to hear.

719
00:41:55,285 --> 00:41:56,328
Oh.

720
00:41:56,411 --> 00:42:00,123
By the way, do you happen to know
an employee by the name of Lee Young-hun?

721
00:42:00,623 --> 00:42:02,667
Hmm… I don't. Why?

722
00:42:02,751 --> 00:42:03,835
[sighs]

723
00:42:03,918 --> 00:42:05,545
I heard that he was forced into doing

724
00:42:05,628 --> 00:42:08,798
a product launch presentation by his boss…

725
00:42:08,882 --> 00:42:11,468
[clicks tongue] …and had a panic attack.

726
00:42:11,551 --> 00:42:12,886
Goodness.

727
00:42:12,969 --> 00:42:16,056
So I thought that
if you knew his contact number,

728
00:42:16,556 --> 00:42:18,641
maybe I could send him
a friendly message of support.

729
00:42:18,725 --> 00:42:23,563
[chuckles] Well, Mr. Ko,
that's very considerate of you.

730
00:42:25,440 --> 00:42:27,650
Well, a company doesn't just run itself.

731
00:42:28,818 --> 00:42:31,363
Us managers
must always look after everyone.

732
00:42:31,446 --> 00:42:33,365
Wouldn't you agree,

733
00:42:33,448 --> 00:42:34,949
my dear Mr. Kang?

734
00:42:40,372 --> 00:42:41,831
[Young-sam sighs]

735
00:42:46,628 --> 00:42:48,630
[phone ringing]

736
00:42:49,297 --> 00:42:50,298
Hmm?

737
00:42:55,887 --> 00:42:57,389
Lee Young-hun speaking.

738
00:43:01,351 --> 00:43:02,352
I see.

739
00:43:10,276 --> 00:43:11,486
[phone buzzing]

740
00:43:15,240 --> 00:43:16,616
Who's this?

741
00:43:20,161 --> 00:43:21,204
Hello?

742
00:43:21,287 --> 00:43:23,373
[TA] This is my number.
Make sure you save it.

743
00:43:23,456 --> 00:43:24,749
And who are you?

744
00:43:24,833 --> 00:43:26,543
I need to wear that hat tomorrow.

745
00:43:26,626 --> 00:43:28,169
Can you bring it to me after class?

746
00:43:28,253 --> 00:43:29,254
[scoffs]

747
00:43:30,839 --> 00:43:32,841
[electronic music playing]

748
00:44:27,395 --> 00:44:28,938
[No-ah] Thanks for the hat.

749
00:44:29,022 --> 00:44:30,648
But giving it to me

750
00:44:30,732 --> 00:44:33,568
and then asking for it back
is a bit uncalled for.

751
00:44:33,651 --> 00:44:35,236
You wouldn't have come
if I'd just asked you to.

752
00:44:35,320 --> 00:44:36,863
What are you trying to pull here?

753
00:44:36,946 --> 00:44:38,239
I'm saying we should hang out.

754
00:44:38,323 --> 00:44:39,449
How old are you?

755
00:44:40,074 --> 00:44:41,659
Twenty-three, and you, No-ah?

756
00:44:41,743 --> 00:44:43,119
Excuse me?

757
00:44:43,203 --> 00:44:45,413
Wow, seriously?

758
00:44:46,372 --> 00:44:48,416
I'm 29 years old.

759
00:44:49,792 --> 00:44:50,793
I see.

760
00:44:51,377 --> 00:44:53,463
All right, No-ah. Uh, want a drink?

761
00:44:59,135 --> 00:45:00,136
[No-ah sighs]

762
00:45:01,554 --> 00:45:03,932
Oh? That looks like No-ah's boyfriend.

763
00:45:18,154 --> 00:45:20,823
[sighs, groans] You scared me.

764
00:45:28,164 --> 00:45:29,165
[groans]

765
00:45:32,877 --> 00:45:34,170
He sure does.

766
00:45:35,255 --> 00:45:36,256
Wait a minute.

767
00:45:37,549 --> 00:45:39,300
But how would you even know that, huh?

768
00:45:41,094 --> 00:45:43,263
Did… D-Did you see?

769
00:45:44,389 --> 00:45:45,890
Just how much of it?

770
00:45:46,516 --> 00:45:47,517
Well…

771
00:45:48,351 --> 00:45:49,561
How much did I see?

772
00:45:49,644 --> 00:45:51,271
[No-ah] Did you cheat on me?

773
00:45:51,354 --> 00:45:52,730
[Goo-won] It's not like that.

774
00:45:53,606 --> 00:45:55,108
She doesn't even know I like her.

775
00:45:55,191 --> 00:45:56,651
And I'm not telling her.

776
00:45:56,734 --> 00:45:59,821
But how could I keep seeing you
when I'm feeling like this?

777
00:46:00,405 --> 00:46:01,906
If we were to get married,

778
00:46:01,990 --> 00:46:03,449
I'd just be lying to you.

779
00:46:03,533 --> 00:46:06,077
Wow. He's getting clocked
if he keeps that up.

780
00:46:06,661 --> 00:46:07,996
[patron] What's wrong with him?

781
00:46:08,705 --> 00:46:10,456
That's it. Grab the cup and throw it.

782
00:46:14,002 --> 00:46:15,670
[Goo-won] What do you think you're doing?

783
00:46:15,753 --> 00:46:17,338
[No-ah] I'm begging you right now.

784
00:46:17,839 --> 00:46:20,633
I'll forgive you, but take it back.

785
00:46:20,717 --> 00:46:22,010
No-ah, just get up.

786
00:46:22,093 --> 00:46:24,387
Then just tell me
you didn't mean what you said!

787
00:46:24,470 --> 00:46:25,471
[Goo-won] I'm sorry.

788
00:46:25,555 --> 00:46:27,807
I'll carry this guilt forever.

789
00:46:28,600 --> 00:46:30,893
[No-ah sobbing]

790
00:46:43,823 --> 00:46:45,450
[groans]

791
00:46:46,909 --> 00:46:48,411
You saw the whole thing.

792
00:46:48,995 --> 00:46:50,204
I did, yeah.

793
00:46:50,288 --> 00:46:52,540
[groans] I can't believe this.

794
00:46:55,209 --> 00:46:56,085
Want revenge?

795
00:46:57,045 --> 00:46:57,879
What?

796
00:46:57,962 --> 00:47:00,548
They say you should enjoy life
after you get revenge.

797
00:47:00,632 --> 00:47:02,842
Let's do it. Get revenge on that bastard.

798
00:47:04,636 --> 00:47:05,470
Let's do it?

799
00:47:05,553 --> 00:47:07,347
Mm-hmm. No-ah and me.

800
00:47:07,430 --> 00:47:08,640
Let's do it.

801
00:47:11,726 --> 00:47:14,646
You're not exactly
in your right mind either, are you?

802
00:47:15,480 --> 00:47:17,231
[clicks tongue, sighs] Fine.

803
00:47:21,778 --> 00:47:22,945
[screams]

804
00:47:23,029 --> 00:47:24,030
[phone buzzes]

805
00:47:29,243 --> 00:47:31,788
[friend 1] Hey, Yoon No-ah!
Did you break up with Goo-won?

806
00:47:35,458 --> 00:47:36,542
[No-ah] Where did you hear that?

807
00:47:37,543 --> 00:47:39,504
Goo-won couldn't keep quiet
in his group chat.

808
00:47:39,587 --> 00:47:41,422
-[scoffs] Whoa.
-Said he broke up with you,

809
00:47:41,506 --> 00:47:43,549
but you stalked him
and even got on your knees.

810
00:47:44,550 --> 00:47:46,386
[friend 2] Is it true? Why would you?

811
00:47:47,387 --> 00:47:49,055
[No-ah] I guess he left
that part out, huh,

812
00:47:49,138 --> 00:47:50,973
that he dumped me
because he cheated on me?

813
00:47:51,057 --> 00:47:52,433
[friend 3] Seriously?

814
00:47:52,517 --> 00:47:54,018
Pathetic excuse for a human.

815
00:47:54,102 --> 00:47:55,978
[friend 1] Hey,
I'm telling the guys about this, okay?

816
00:47:56,062 --> 00:47:57,063
[No-ah] Okay.

817
00:47:59,649 --> 00:48:01,651
[electronic music continues]

818
00:48:07,657 --> 00:48:08,700
[groans]

819
00:48:09,617 --> 00:48:11,536
Let's do it. Revenge.

820
00:48:11,619 --> 00:48:12,620
Where do we start then?

821
00:48:13,663 --> 00:48:15,123
I knew you'd be fun.

822
00:48:19,794 --> 00:48:21,838
Yes, then I'll proceed accordingly.

823
00:48:22,922 --> 00:48:24,674
I'll see you at the venue tomorrow.

824
00:48:26,634 --> 00:48:28,469
The presentation's tomorrow.

825
00:48:28,553 --> 00:48:29,929
You shouldn't still be working.

826
00:48:30,012 --> 00:48:31,139
Go home now.

827
00:48:31,723 --> 00:48:32,974
-Right.
-[typing]

828
00:48:33,057 --> 00:48:35,768
I'll just send this email. Okay.

829
00:48:57,248 --> 00:48:58,624
Come on, stand up.

830
00:48:59,125 --> 00:49:00,209
I'll take you home now.

831
00:49:04,338 --> 00:49:06,382
[groaning] Just a moment.
I need the bathroom.

832
00:49:08,092 --> 00:49:09,343
[groans]

833
00:49:10,386 --> 00:49:11,554
Ms. Cha!

834
00:49:13,681 --> 00:49:15,641
[sighs] I feel like throwing up.

835
00:49:16,809 --> 00:49:18,770
I warned you about junk food.

836
00:49:18,853 --> 00:49:20,521
The coffee and sugary drinks!

837
00:49:21,022 --> 00:49:22,023
Sorry?

838
00:49:22,857 --> 00:49:23,858
Please forgive me.

839
00:49:28,529 --> 00:49:29,739
[groans]

840
00:49:37,038 --> 00:49:38,414
Let's go to the hospital.

841
00:49:38,498 --> 00:49:39,832
[sighs] Mr. Kang.

842
00:49:40,875 --> 00:49:42,877
Just let me hit "send" on that email.

843
00:49:49,759 --> 00:49:51,677
SEND

844
00:49:51,761 --> 00:49:52,595
EMAIL SENT SUCCESSFULLY

845
00:49:55,598 --> 00:49:56,933
[sighing]

846
00:49:57,016 --> 00:49:58,017
Mr. Kang.

847
00:49:58,518 --> 00:50:01,312
I'd like to go home, not the hospital.

848
00:50:01,395 --> 00:50:03,648
That won't do. I'll get you to the ER.

849
00:50:03,731 --> 00:50:04,816
Oh, no.

850
00:50:04,899 --> 00:50:06,901
No, this is just period cramps.

851
00:50:08,653 --> 00:50:11,531
I forgot to bring painkillers from home,
so that's all.

852
00:50:14,242 --> 00:50:16,160
All right, I understand.

853
00:50:28,798 --> 00:50:31,050
Are you sure painkillers
will be enough though?

854
00:50:31,551 --> 00:50:32,677
Mm-hmm.

855
00:50:33,261 --> 00:50:34,720
I can still take you to the hospital.

856
00:50:34,804 --> 00:50:37,223
I'll be fine in no time, don't worry.

857
00:50:37,807 --> 00:50:38,808
I didn't know…

858
00:50:40,059 --> 00:50:42,478
you could pass out from period cramps.

859
00:50:43,187 --> 00:50:45,523
It's just mine are particularly bad.

860
00:50:47,692 --> 00:50:49,360
Thank you so much,

861
00:50:50,194 --> 00:50:51,404
Mr. Kang.

862
00:51:27,148 --> 00:51:28,649
[sighs]

863
00:51:38,075 --> 00:51:38,993
[Ji-yoon] Ga-eul?

864
00:51:40,119 --> 00:51:43,039
Hey, why are you here?

865
00:51:45,499 --> 00:51:46,626
You awake?

866
00:51:48,336 --> 00:51:49,921
Stay in bed longer.

867
00:51:53,883 --> 00:51:56,302
Guess he wants to be all polite
now that we broke up.

868
00:51:56,385 --> 00:51:58,179
I couldn't use your kitchen,

869
00:51:58,846 --> 00:51:59,847
so I bought this.

870
00:52:00,598 --> 00:52:03,017
When you wake up,
make sure you eat the porridge

871
00:52:03,100 --> 00:52:04,435
and then the medication.

872
00:52:05,811 --> 00:52:06,979
Don't take it on an empty stomach.

873
00:52:10,775 --> 00:52:12,652
And even if you feel better after,

874
00:52:13,945 --> 00:52:16,822
go to the hospital.
And make sure you get checked out.

875
00:52:19,533 --> 00:52:20,785
Ga-eul.

876
00:52:30,544 --> 00:52:32,004
Looks like your fever came down.

877
00:52:34,590 --> 00:52:35,675
I'm sorry.

878
00:52:48,938 --> 00:52:49,939
[chuckles]

879
00:52:51,983 --> 00:52:54,485
Well, that's a bit upsetting.

880
00:52:58,406 --> 00:52:59,573
[Ji-yoon] Mr. Kang?

881
00:53:12,586 --> 00:53:13,754
Don't be sick.

882
00:53:15,840 --> 00:53:18,217
[Ji-yoon] Is this a dream?

883
00:53:19,885 --> 00:53:22,513
Mr. Kang and his kind voice.

884
00:53:23,723 --> 00:53:25,766
And his warm touch…

885
00:53:38,696 --> 00:53:40,740
[groans]

886
00:53:44,118 --> 00:53:45,369
[groans]

887
00:53:46,662 --> 00:53:49,373
[sighs] It was especially bad this time.

888
00:53:51,208 --> 00:53:53,335
I should see a doctor or something.

889
00:53:53,419 --> 00:53:55,629
[groans] The presentation prep is really…

890
00:53:56,464 --> 00:53:57,548
[gasps]

891
00:53:58,299 --> 00:53:59,467
Oh, no.

892
00:53:59,550 --> 00:54:02,344
It has become
the most personal space we have.

893
00:54:02,428 --> 00:54:03,971
A reflection of who we are

894
00:54:04,597 --> 00:54:06,223
and how we choose to live.

895
00:54:06,307 --> 00:54:08,184
-Is Cha Ji-yoon not here?
-[sighs]

896
00:54:09,935 --> 00:54:11,520
Another person driven over the edge.

897
00:54:11,604 --> 00:54:13,230
Don't you think this is too far?

898
00:54:13,314 --> 00:54:15,608
How could he work someone
to the point of collapse?

899
00:54:15,691 --> 00:54:18,986
One missing screw won't affect
this giant corporation at all,

900
00:54:19,070 --> 00:54:20,905
because there are always spare parts.

901
00:54:21,405 --> 00:54:23,824
And on top of that,
they're stronger and tighter.

902
00:54:23,908 --> 00:54:25,159
I'll look into it right away.

903
00:54:25,242 --> 00:54:26,243
Thanks.

904
00:54:30,790 --> 00:54:33,667
[upbeat music playing]

905
00:54:33,751 --> 00:54:35,544
SAEUM'S SPHERE ICE REFRIGERATOR
NEW PRODUCT

906
00:54:35,628 --> 00:54:36,587
SAEUM'S SPHERE ICE REFRIGERATOR

907
00:54:52,311 --> 00:54:53,729
How are you?

908
00:54:53,813 --> 00:54:54,897
Good.

909
00:55:07,409 --> 00:55:09,411
Home is no longer just where we live.

910
00:55:09,495 --> 00:55:10,913
[Ji-yoon] Mr. Kang!

911
00:55:14,583 --> 00:55:15,709
Are you okay?

912
00:55:15,793 --> 00:55:19,004
I know it's out of line,
but may I do the presentation?

913
00:55:21,632 --> 00:55:22,842
Please go ahead.

914
00:55:22,925 --> 00:55:24,635
I didn't want to make a mistake.

915
00:55:25,594 --> 00:55:29,098
No one else here knows more about
the ice sphere fridge than you, Ms. Cha.

916
00:55:29,181 --> 00:55:30,182
And now…

917
00:55:31,600 --> 00:55:33,477
go out there and show off your skills.

918
00:55:36,021 --> 00:55:37,022
Sir.

919
00:55:44,488 --> 00:55:45,489
Cha Ji-yoon…

920
00:56:00,462 --> 00:56:03,382
Home is no longer just where we live.

921
00:56:03,883 --> 00:56:07,595
It has become
the most personal space we have.

922
00:56:07,678 --> 00:56:11,098
A reflection of who we are
and how we choose to live.

923
00:56:11,682 --> 00:56:14,268
After a long day, we unwind at home

924
00:56:14,351 --> 00:56:16,061
with a glass of whiskey.

925
00:56:16,145 --> 00:56:18,397
In the evening, friends gather.

926
00:56:18,480 --> 00:56:20,983
Good food, easy conversation,

927
00:56:21,066 --> 00:56:23,027
and ice-cold cocktails.

928
00:56:23,611 --> 00:56:25,154
At Saeum Electronics,

929
00:56:25,237 --> 00:56:27,573
we asked ourselves a simple question.

930
00:56:28,324 --> 00:56:30,576
"What makes this moment

931
00:56:30,659 --> 00:56:32,119
truly complete?"

932
00:56:34,872 --> 00:56:36,916
The answer was

933
00:56:37,541 --> 00:56:38,792
ice.

934
00:56:39,460 --> 00:56:40,753
But not just any ice.

935
00:56:41,378 --> 00:56:43,756
A crystal-clear sphere of ice.

936
00:56:43,839 --> 00:56:48,093
Once found only
in the world's finest lounges.

937
00:56:48,886 --> 00:56:53,390
We've made it possible
to create this ice at home,

938
00:56:54,016 --> 00:56:55,726
using our proprietary

939
00:56:56,518 --> 00:56:59,230
reverse icicle freezing technology,

940
00:56:59,313 --> 00:57:00,898
freezing water drop by drop.

941
00:57:01,565 --> 00:57:04,485
With less surface area
in contact with your drink,

942
00:57:05,402 --> 00:57:08,405
the ice melts slowly,

943
00:57:08,489 --> 00:57:10,157
preserving flavor longer.

944
00:57:11,408 --> 00:57:12,701
And above all,

945
00:57:13,452 --> 00:57:14,495
it's beautiful.

946
00:57:16,956 --> 00:57:18,040
That moment,

947
00:57:19,291 --> 00:57:22,544
when a perfectly formed sphere of ice
drops into your glass…

948
00:57:22,628 --> 00:57:25,547
[microphone feedback]

949
00:57:34,223 --> 00:57:36,517
[sighs, breathing shakily]

950
00:57:40,271 --> 00:57:42,356
[Young-sam]
Give me a break. Are you serious?

951
00:57:42,439 --> 00:57:45,442
A senior associate can't handle
a product launch presentation!

952
00:57:45,526 --> 00:57:46,819
[employee] We'll wait and see

953
00:57:47,319 --> 00:57:50,823
whether Ms. Cha becomes another victim
of Three-No-Man or not.

954
00:57:57,454 --> 00:57:59,915
[breathes shakily]

955
00:58:02,960 --> 00:58:04,628
[sharply exhales]

956
00:58:06,755 --> 00:58:08,090
[Si-woo] What's wrong with the fences?

957
00:58:08,173 --> 00:58:09,633
A single hit could turn the game.

958
00:58:09,717 --> 00:58:12,428
I'd tell them to be aggressive
even if he ends up striking out.

959
00:58:12,511 --> 00:58:14,847
Forget the sacrifice bunts,
just be a hero.

960
00:58:15,431 --> 00:58:17,141
When you get nervous, remember…

961
00:58:17,224 --> 00:58:19,310
[breathes deeply]

962
00:58:19,393 --> 00:58:20,644
…and you'll know the answer.

963
00:58:20,728 --> 00:58:22,396
Is that your sign, Coach?

964
00:58:22,479 --> 00:58:23,480
Yes.

965
00:58:24,898 --> 00:58:26,567
[sharply exhales]

966
00:58:38,162 --> 00:58:40,331
…transforms an ordinary drink

967
00:58:40,414 --> 00:58:41,874
into an experience.

968
00:58:42,416 --> 00:58:46,045
Today, we are proud
to bring that experience

969
00:58:46,128 --> 00:58:47,129
into your home.

970
00:58:49,214 --> 00:58:53,844
We present to you
the all-new SAEUM Ice Sphere Refrigerator.

971
00:58:59,266 --> 00:59:01,101
[pop music playing]

972
00:59:15,115 --> 00:59:18,327
[sighs] What can I say,
Ms. Cha is killing it up there.

973
00:59:18,410 --> 00:59:21,121
Yeah, I'm jealous as hell. [chuckles]

974
00:59:22,039 --> 00:59:24,458
Wasn't that woman
a senior associate on your team?

975
00:59:24,541 --> 00:59:26,085
Why'd you send her to the task force?

976
00:59:26,168 --> 00:59:28,837
She's efficient,
so she's great to delegate to.

977
00:59:28,921 --> 00:59:31,090
But there's a ceiling
to how far you could take her.

978
00:59:31,173 --> 00:59:33,258
And she leaves work at 6:00 on the dot.

979
00:59:33,342 --> 00:59:36,178
Who cares about her leaving right on time
if she's good at what she does?

980
00:59:36,261 --> 00:59:38,931
You're such a bad judge of character.

981
00:59:39,014 --> 00:59:41,642
[sighs] No wonder you're stuck
in management.

982
00:59:43,519 --> 00:59:46,355
Wow, it was received
so much better than I expected.

983
00:59:46,438 --> 00:59:48,482
Oh. Just a moment.

984
00:59:48,982 --> 00:59:49,983
Excuse me.

985
00:59:50,859 --> 00:59:51,944
Great work.

986
00:59:52,486 --> 00:59:55,739
Thanks to both of you, the new product
has become highly anticipated.

987
00:59:55,823 --> 00:59:56,824
[chuckles]

988
00:59:56,907 --> 00:59:59,201
Please join us. Let's get dinner together.

989
00:59:59,284 --> 01:00:00,369
We have prior plans.

990
01:00:02,246 --> 01:00:03,956
Oh… Oh, oh. Sure, sure, sure.

991
01:00:04,039 --> 01:00:05,249
All right.

992
01:00:05,332 --> 01:00:07,709
Well, then I look forward
to your next project.

993
01:00:07,793 --> 01:00:09,545
Goodbye. [chuckles]

994
01:00:10,921 --> 01:00:12,548
Looks like it's just us. [chuckles]

995
01:00:12,631 --> 01:00:13,841
-You sure?
-Yes.

996
01:00:13,924 --> 01:00:15,801
-All right.
-[clicks tongue] Oh, it's fine.

997
01:00:17,386 --> 01:00:18,971
What do you mean, plans?

998
01:00:19,054 --> 01:00:22,307
What kind of plans would make you
refuse dinner with the President?

999
01:00:22,391 --> 01:00:23,809
We have a team dinner.

1000
01:00:24,810 --> 01:00:25,811
What?

1001
01:00:27,563 --> 01:00:29,148
Is there anything you're craving?

1002
01:00:29,982 --> 01:00:32,651
I would always just choose chicken?

1003
01:00:33,819 --> 01:00:34,820
Sounds good.

1004
01:00:35,487 --> 01:00:36,905
Really? [chuckles]

1005
01:00:43,620 --> 01:00:46,915
Everyone knows chicken is better fried.

1006
01:00:50,919 --> 01:00:54,006
Fried food on an empty stomach's
not good for you.

1007
01:00:54,798 --> 01:00:56,967
-Did you eat the porridge?
-No.

1008
01:00:59,344 --> 01:01:01,513
But it's okay, I'm feeling fine right now.

1009
01:01:02,014 --> 01:01:05,309
Well, it was particularly bad
this time… [chuckles]

1010
01:01:05,392 --> 01:01:07,352
…but it's a very familiar kind of pain.

1011
01:01:07,436 --> 01:01:09,313
Corporate slaves can't get sick.

1012
01:01:09,396 --> 01:01:12,024
Reduce your coffee intake,
start working out, eat better,

1013
01:01:12,107 --> 01:01:13,358
and make sure you see a doctor.

1014
01:01:14,526 --> 01:01:16,820
Oh, do you take any vitamins at all?

1015
01:01:18,030 --> 01:01:19,031
I don't.

1016
01:01:19,114 --> 01:01:21,658
In that case,
next time we'll be buying vitamins.

1017
01:01:23,827 --> 01:01:25,078
[Ji-yoon] Has there ever been

1018
01:01:25,162 --> 01:01:27,998
a man in my life
who was this concerned about my health?

1019
01:01:29,958 --> 01:01:30,959
Well then?

1020
01:01:32,127 --> 01:01:33,170
Eat up.

1021
01:01:43,639 --> 01:01:45,849
What is it? Does it taste bad?

1022
01:01:47,226 --> 01:01:48,393
No.

1023
01:01:48,477 --> 01:01:49,478
It's delicious.

1024
01:01:51,813 --> 01:01:52,981
Would you like a popsicle?

1025
01:01:54,149 --> 01:01:56,443
Tell you what, you can be the wind.

1026
01:01:56,527 --> 01:01:57,903
And I'll be the sun.

1027
01:02:06,119 --> 01:02:07,120
I got it.

1028
01:02:10,749 --> 01:02:11,875
Brows of truth.

1029
01:02:13,043 --> 01:02:15,879
You actually frown
when you like something, don't you?

1030
01:02:15,963 --> 01:02:17,297
Now I get it.

1031
01:02:17,381 --> 01:02:20,509
I had no idea, and it was making me
anxious because you kept frowning at me.

1032
01:02:20,592 --> 01:02:23,095
Did I frown that often at you though?

1033
01:02:23,178 --> 01:02:24,179
Yes.

1034
01:02:25,430 --> 01:02:26,431
Mmm…

1035
01:02:28,058 --> 01:02:29,726
I guess you won me over then.

1036
01:02:31,103 --> 01:02:33,730
[gentle pop music playing]

1037
01:02:48,870 --> 01:02:49,955
It's yummy.

1038
01:03:10,892 --> 01:03:13,437
[Si-woo] Don't forget the porridge
and the meds.

1039
01:03:19,610 --> 01:03:20,694
Don't be sick.

1040
01:03:22,988 --> 01:03:24,156
[Ji-yoon] It wasn't a dream.

1041
01:03:43,008 --> 01:03:44,718
WE'RE A TEAM

1042
01:04:12,079 --> 01:04:14,081
[typing]

1043
01:04:16,208 --> 01:04:18,085
[person] Did you make it
to work okay today?

1044
01:04:19,378 --> 01:04:21,713
Aren't the trees
in front of the office so beautiful?

1045
01:04:21,797 --> 01:04:23,340
[passengers exclaiming]

1046
01:04:31,598 --> 01:04:33,141
[phone buzzes]

1047
01:04:33,642 --> 01:04:35,852
[Kee-tae] Hey!
Have you checked the company forum?

1048
01:04:39,690 --> 01:04:41,108
[person] Hello, everyone.

1049
01:04:41,733 --> 01:04:44,611
My name is Lee Young-hun.
I'm in my ninth year at SAEUM

1050
01:04:44,695 --> 01:04:46,571
and currently on a leave of absence.

1051
01:04:48,365 --> 01:04:50,117
Between sick leave and parental leave,

1052
01:04:50,200 --> 01:04:53,370
I have spent almost
three whole years away from work.

1053
01:04:53,870 --> 01:04:55,455
One day, three years ago,

1054
01:04:55,539 --> 01:04:58,500
I encountered an unwelcome guest
in the form of panic disorder.

1055
01:04:59,000 --> 01:05:01,795
But I couldn't really
tell anyone at the time.

1056
01:05:01,878 --> 01:05:03,588
I didn't want to be seen as weak.

1057
01:05:04,923 --> 01:05:07,092
Because having a newborn at home

1058
01:05:07,175 --> 01:05:09,636
meant I couldn't risk
jeopardizing my career.

1059
01:05:11,012 --> 01:05:14,182
And then, finally, someone found me
sitting alone in a stairwell…

1060
01:05:14,683 --> 01:05:15,684
This is Kang Si-woo.

1061
01:05:15,767 --> 01:05:17,102
…hyperventilating and in pain.

1062
01:05:17,185 --> 01:05:20,397
Hey, Mom. Hi, yeah, it's me.
Apparently, Han-gyeol is not doing well…

1063
01:05:20,480 --> 01:05:22,482
[Young-hun] He sat me down
and gave me a serious talk.

1064
01:05:23,650 --> 01:05:24,860
Mom, the kid is sick.

1065
01:05:24,943 --> 01:05:26,445
Uh, I'll take half the day off…

1066
01:05:26,528 --> 01:05:28,238
[Young-hun] He just told me to stop…

1067
01:05:28,864 --> 01:05:30,240
to stop working right away

1068
01:05:31,074 --> 01:05:32,576
and to take care of myself.

1069
01:05:33,285 --> 01:05:35,495
I walked out that very same day,

1070
01:05:36,455 --> 01:05:39,458
leaving him to deal
with the launch presentation

1071
01:05:39,541 --> 01:05:41,543
I had stubbornly insisted on doing.

1072
01:05:43,128 --> 01:05:45,756
Someone from the company
emailed me recently.

1073
01:05:46,715 --> 01:05:49,551
And asked me to clear up
the misunderstandings about him at work.

1074
01:05:50,177 --> 01:05:52,888
That's when I found out
about the rumors about him.

1075
01:05:54,181 --> 01:05:55,182
Yeah,

1076
01:05:55,682 --> 01:05:57,225
someone who doesn't smile often,

1077
01:05:57,309 --> 01:05:58,560
a man of few words,

1078
01:05:58,643 --> 01:06:00,145
and doesn't apologize.

1079
01:06:00,228 --> 01:06:01,813
He is Three-No-Man.

1080
01:06:03,023 --> 01:06:05,609
To some, he may be
the worst boss imaginable.

1081
01:06:06,985 --> 01:06:08,069
But to me,

1082
01:06:09,154 --> 01:06:13,116
he is a unicorn of a boss
who actually saved my life.

1083
01:06:13,742 --> 01:06:15,035
I can't wait to see you,

1084
01:06:15,577 --> 01:06:16,828
Mr. Kang Si-woo.

1085
01:06:31,551 --> 01:06:32,552
[Soo-jin] Si-woo.

1086
01:06:49,903 --> 01:06:51,613
[Ji-yoon] Why are they…

1087
01:06:54,324 --> 01:06:57,369
Did they choose to stay friends
after breaking up?

1088
01:07:01,665 --> 01:07:02,666
But…

1089
01:07:03,166 --> 01:07:04,960
Why am I feeling this way?

1090
01:07:08,338 --> 01:07:10,340
[pop music playing]

1091
01:07:41,580 --> 01:07:44,082
[Ji-yoon] Do I? Mr. Kang?

1092
01:07:45,792 --> 01:07:47,836
So then, if you got married
and then divorced,

1093
01:07:47,919 --> 01:07:49,880
what would you call your ex-husband?

1094
01:07:49,963 --> 01:07:51,464
Where are we, in Hollywood?

1095
01:07:51,548 --> 01:07:53,049
[Si-woo] We will run
a second round of recruitment.

1096
01:07:53,133 --> 01:07:54,759
-Hello there, sir!
-I'll do it.

1097
01:07:54,843 --> 01:07:56,469
No. I-I mean, I'll try.

1098
01:07:56,553 --> 01:07:58,138
[Ji-yoon] They may have a crush.

1099
01:07:58,221 --> 01:08:00,181
Taking on a true man of mystery…

1100
01:08:00,891 --> 01:08:02,684
will give you a whole new thrill.

1101
01:08:03,476 --> 01:08:04,811
Is there a meeting I wasn't aware of?

1102
01:08:04,895 --> 01:08:05,812
WHAT MAKES YOUR HEART FLUTTER?

1103
01:08:08,106 --> 01:08:10,317
[Ji-yoon] Do I make you laugh? Do I, sir?

